	<div id="content-left">	
	
	
<div class="headings">Welcome</div>

<div id="content-left-style">	
Operated by the Mission District Historical Society, the Mission Community Archives serves as a central repository for all community records that document the social, economic, and political development of the District of Mission and the Fraser Valley Regional District Electoral Areas: I (Dewdney-Hatzic Island), J (Nicomen Island Â– Deroche), K (Lake Errock) and L (McConnell Creek-Hatzic Prairie).
<br><br>
The holdings include the records of individuals and families, arts and community organizations, clubs and local businesses and some local government. The archives also maintain a small reference collection pertaining to the history of the municipality, genealogical research, and the administration of archives. 	<br><br>
</div>
<div class="headings-b"></div>

<div id="content-right-style">

<div class="headings-b">Glimpses of the Past: <I>1940s</I></div>
<font size="-2" color="#4C6454"></font>
<br>
<img src="images/2016-05-07-0116-016-013-Hatzic-Swans-Point.jpg" width="600" height="400" alt="">
<br>
<I> Carl Klenk collection / Mission Community Archives</I></font>

<br>
<font size="-2" color="#000000">
<br><font size="-3" color="#4C6454"><b>SWAN'S POINT </b> - a popular summer resort in the Fraser Valley and the Lower Mainland was established by William "Bill" Swan - a veteran of World War I and II - and his wife Lena in 1933 following the conversion of their berry farm into an 8 acre park on the north end of Hatzic Lake. When they sold the property in 1946, they had built up the facilities to include: "25 row boats, a bathhouse, eight cabins ranging from one to three rooms in size and a larger building popular with organized groups" as well as  the orchard as picnic ground (SOURCE: <i> Fraser Valley Record</i>, April 4, 1946:1) 
<br><br>
If you or anyone you know have information about Swan's Point, please <strong><a href="mailto:manager@missionarchives.com">email</a></strong> the archivist, Val Billesberger.

